    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the culture of the Narragansett, an Algonkian-speaking Indian tribe that occupied most of what is now the state of Rhode Island west of Narragansett Bay. Today, the Narragansett largely live in southern Rhode Island as a federally-recognized tribe.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
